3 SECTION 3. NEW AND VACANT FTE POOL - LIMITATION - TRANSFER REQUEST. The
4 department of public instruction, center for distance education, state library, school for the deaf,
5 and North Dakota vision services - school for the blind may not spend funds appropriated in the
6 new and vacant FTE pool line item in section 1 of this Act, but may request the office of
7 management and budget to transfer funds from the new and vacant FTE pool line item to the
8 salaries and wages line item or the center for distance education line item within each
9 respective subdivision in accordance with the guidelines and reporting provisions included in
10 House Bill No. 1015, as approved by the sixty-ninth legislative assembly.
11 SECTION 4. APPROPRIATION - TUITION APPORTIONMENT. The sum of $595,677,350,
12 included in the integrated formula payments line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act, is
13 from the state tuition fund in the state treasury. Any additional amount in the state tuition fund
14 that becomes available for distribution to public schools is appropriated to the department of
15 public instruction for that purpose for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30,
16 2027.
17 SECTION 5. OTHER FUNDS - FOUNDATION AID STABILIZATION FUND. The other
18 funds line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act includes the sum of $133,000,000 from
19 the foundation aid stabilization fund for integrated formula payments.
20 SECTION 6. OTHER FUNDS - STRATEGIC INVESTMENT AND IMPROVEMENTS FUND.
21 The other funds line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act includes the sum of $5,750,000
22 from the strategic investment and improvements fund for one-time program grants, relating to
23 dyslexia training, a statewide reading tool, a teacher retention program, school board training,
24 and a Native American essential understandings program and book series.
25 SECTION 7. INTEGRATED FORMULA PAYMENTS AND SPECIAL EDUCATION
26 CONTRACTS EXPENDITURE AUTHORITY. The superintendent of public instruction may
27 expend funds included in the integrated formula payments and grants - special education
28 contracts line items in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act for paying grants for educational
29 services that were due in the 2023-25 biennium but which were not filed, claimed, or properly
30 supported by the education provider until after June 30, 2025. To be reimbursed under this
