3 SECTION 8. GIFTED AND TALENTED PROGRAM. The sum of $800,000, included in the
4 integrated formula payments line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act, must be
5 distributed to reimburse school districts or special education units for gifted and talented
6 programs upon the submission of an application that is approved in accordance with guidelines
7 adopted by the superintendent of public instruction. The superintendent of public instruction
8 shall encourage cooperative efforts for gifted and talented programs among school districts and
9 special education units.
10 SECTION 9. MEDICAID MATCHING FUNDING - WITHHOLDING AND DISTRIBUTION.
11 State school aid payments for special education must be reduced by the amount of matching
12 funds required to be paid by school districts or special education units for students participating
13 in the Medicaid program, for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027.
14 Special education funds equal to the amount of the matching funds required to be paid by the
15 school district or special education unit must be paid by the superintendent of public instruction
16 to the department of health and human services on behalf of the school district or unit.
17 SECTION 10. REGIONAL EDUCATION ASSOCIATIONS - GRANTS - DISTRIBUTION.
18 The integrated formula payments line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act includes
19 $600,000 from the general fund for the purpose of providing annual grants to regional education
20 associations, for the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. An annual
21 grant of $50,000 is provided to each regional education association that exists as of July 1,
22 2025. Regional education associations that merge during the 2025-27 biennium are entitled to
23 the annual grants that would have been paid to each of the member associations.
24 SECTION 11. STUDENT MEALS - GRANTS - DISTRIBUTION. The grants - program
25 grants line item in subdivision 1 of section 1 of this Act includes $7,300,000 from the general
26 fund for the purpose of providing grants to school districts to defray the expenses of providing
27 meals, free of charge, for all students enrolled in public or nonpublic school at or below
28 two hundred twenty-five percent of the federal poverty guideline, for the biennium beginning
29 July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027. The superintendent of public instruction shall develop
30 guidelines and reporting requirements for the grants.
